a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = -34.1"
shows  "floor (abs x) = 34"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $\left\lfloor |{-34.1}|\right\rfloor$. The final Answer is 34
 ### Proof
 We have $|{-34.1}| = 34.1$, so $\lfloor |{-34.1}|\rfloor = \lfloor 34.1\rfloor =\boxed{34}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = -34.1"
shows  "floor (abs x) = 34"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the floor of the absolute value of $-34.1$. The final answer is $34$.
